creator: jon.handiboe@jhuapl.edu
text:
Apache 1.3.24 on RedHat 7.2.  ./httpd -l:

Compiled-in modules:
  http_core.c
  mod_env.c
  mod_log_config.c
  mod_mime.c
  mod_negotiation.c
  mod_status.c
  mod_include.c
  mod_autoindex.c
  mod_dir.c
  mod_cgi.c
  mod_asis.c
  mod_imap.c
  mod_actions.c
  mod_userdir.c
  mod_alias.c
  mod_access.c
  mod_auth.c
  mod_so.c
  mod_setenvif.c

Default http.conf file (IndexOptions FancyIndexing: ReadmeName README).  File
doesn't get displayed in browser.  Other functions of autoindex (AddDescription,
IndexIgnore, AddIcon) all seem to work okay.  Same configuration file running
with apache 1.3.23 install on same system works okay.

jon
